  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Current provisioner for GlusterFS needs a plaintext password in `StorageClass.Parameters`:\n\n``` yaml\nkind: StorageClass\nmetadata:\n  name: slow\nprovisioner: kubernetes.io/glusterfs\nparameters:\n  endpoint: \"glusterfs-cluster\"\n  resturl: \"http://127.0.0.1:8081\"\n  restauthenabled: \"true\"\n  restuser: \"admin\"\n  restuserkey: \"password\"\n```\n\nThere should be a secret to hold the password.\n\nIn addition, as agreed in #30897, the configuration parameters from StorageClass should be stored in provisioned  PVs as annotations, so the class can be modified/deleted without blocking deletion of dynamically provisioned volumes.\n\n Proposing P1: This is a new API in 1.4, it would be better to fix it before we release it.\n",
